                <p><pb/><hi rend="center"><hi rend="italic">Philadelphia, Aug</hi>. 5.</hi></p>
                <p>We are happy in informing our readers, that <lb/>in the memory of the oldest man among us a <lb/>more plentiful year has not been known than the <lb/>present. Neither mildew nor fly has affected the <lb/>wheat; the grain is heavy, and full, and in large <lb/>quantities. The other grains are likewise plen<lb break="no"/>tiful, and of an excellent quality. Such distin<lb break="no"/>guished favours call for the gratitude of the in<lb break="no"/>habitants of the United Sates, to the great Au<lb break="no"/>thor of Nature; especially when these blessings of <lb/>nature are connected in the same year with deli<lb break="no"/>verance from anarchy, and with the establishment <lb/>of a wise, free, and just government.</p>
